{
  "stem": "27507.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, of course there were, but relatively few, and they must have moved out.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know precisely details about that, but they must have moved out.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But as I said, that area would have been some-- a large part of that area must have been already before the war something like maybe almost 100% Jewish, large parts of it.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It depends where because certain areas like what I said, Nalewki and the northern parts of it were almost only Jewish, I think.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But the other streets, like in the sm-- what was called small ghetto, they were-- it was mixed.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I think that was probably something like there might have been quite a large Polish population in some areas.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But the majority was-- was Jewish even then.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no, no.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They had to leave.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The ghetto was-- was-- [NON-ENGLISH], Jewish-- Jewish living area.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was-- it was absolutely only Jews were living there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were no Poles living in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was a church in the ghetto, or maybe more than one, but I remember that there was one in Leszno, which is actually one of the main streets.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there was the church which was, I think, all the time of the ghetto was being used because there were a number of converted Jews-- Jews who converted to Christianity before the war.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And because the Germans were treating the Jews on their-- according to their racial background and not religious one, they were-- they had to move into ghetto even if they were Christian.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I remember that pl-- that church because it had a garden next to it, and I-- the garden was open.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I-- and gardens were almost nonexistent in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
